  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study evaluates the efficacy of 10 mg/day Lu AF35700 on symptoms of schizophrenia in
      patients with early-in-disease (ED) or late-in-disease (LD) treatment-resistant schizophrenia
      (TRS)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In the study, patients will receive risperidone (4-6 mg/day), or, if recently failed on
      risperidone, olanzapine (15-20mg/day). Later during the study, patients will be randomized to
      either receive Lu AF35700 (10 mg/day), or continue their treatment with risperidone or
      olanzapine.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
